>> meta [
  title="Responsive Layout"
  description="Demonstrates mobile-first responsive overrides"
]

>> style [preset=none]

>> document:
  > section [id=products]:
    > heading.2: Featured products <

    % Mobile-first grid: 1 column base, 2 at tablet width, 4 at desktop width.
    % Gap also increases at larger viewports.
    > grid [
        cols=1 ^(500px)=2 ^(1024px)=4
        gap=1rem gap^(768px)=2rem gap^(1024px)=4rem
      ]:
      > card: Product A <
      > card: Product B <
      > card: Product C <
      > card: Product D <
    < grid
  < section

  > section [id=sidebar-layout]:
    > heading.2: Article page <

    % Explicit bindings when overrides are interleaved with multiple base
    % attributes. The explicit form removes any doubt about what's being
    % overridden at which breakpoint.
    > group [
        layout=column
        layout^(900px)=row
        gap=md
        gap^(900px)=xl
        align=stretch
      ]:
      > article:
        > heading.3: Main content <
        > text: The article body goes here. <
      <
      > aside:
        > heading.4: Related <
        > list [list.number]:
          - First related item
          - Second related item
        <
      <
    < group
  < section

  > section [id="test-section"]:
    > heading.2: Test section <
    > grid [cols^(780px)=2 ^(1024px)=4]:
      > group:
        > heading.3: Test group <
        > text: This is a test group. <
      <
      > group:
        > heading.3: Test group <
        > text: This is a test group. <
      <
    < grid
  < section

  > section [id=hero-responsive]:
    % Implicit overrides work when the binding is obvious from proximity.
    > heading.1 [size=lg ^(768px)=xl ^(1280px)=xxl]:
      Welcome to the site
    <
    > text.lead [size=md ^(768px)=lg]:
      A responsive page that looks good on every screen.
    <
  < section

<< document
